    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>April 12<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Please to send me “The Higher Ministry of Nature by J. Leifchild: Hodder &amp; Stoughton.—”<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>Also please try &amp; get the enclosed for me.—<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>I think that I formerly ordered (do you keep any list? &amp; can you see whether you have already ordered it for me) “A Review of Darwin’s Theory by James Hunter: Appleton &amp; Co. New York.”—<ref target="#foot.f4"/> I am anxious to get this.—</p>
<p>Dear Sir, | Yours faithfully | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">2.1 try] <hi rend="italic">after del illeg</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n2">3.1 can you] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n3">3.2 for me] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the reference to <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_4673.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Leifchild 1872</ref> (see n. 2, below).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2874.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">John Roby Leifchild’s</ref> book (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_4673.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Leifchild 1872</ref>) was published in March 1872 (<hi rend="italic">Publishers’ circular</hi>, 16 March 1872, p. 177). Leifchild was the author of critical reviews of CD’s works in the <hi rend="italic">Athenæum</hi> (see, for example, <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 8, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-2876.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to Asa Gray, 22 July [1860]</ref> and n. 6).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">The enclosure was an advertisement for an offprint of the article ‘The application of Darwinian theory to flowers and the insects which visit them’ (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_5696.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">H. Müller 1871</ref>). The article appeared in the July 1871 issue of <hi rend="italic">American Naturalist</hi>. CD’s annotated copy is in the Darwin Pamphlet Collection–CUL.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">CD refers to an offprint of a review of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> by James B. Hunter that originally appeared in the <hi rend="italic">Journal of Psychological Medicine</hi> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_3957.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Hunter 1871</ref>). CD’s copy of the offprint is in the Darwin Pamphlet Collection–CUL.</note>
        </div>        
            
